168
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,375
A thousand?

169
00:08:48,458 --> 00:08:50,250
I don't know, that's a little--

170
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:51,791
Great! I'm counting on you.

171
00:08:51,875 --> 00:08:53,000
But, w-wait!

172
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:54,750
Good luck with that sport.

173
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,791
You're young.
Just pull an all-nighter.

174
00:08:56,875 --> 00:08:59,125
Oo! I want to have
some dessert, too!

175
00:08:59,208 --> 00:09:02,166
Yeah, me three. Dessert's
my favorite meal of the day!

176
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,666
Isn't that great, Kyohei?

177
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:06,416
No. There's nothing
great about it.

178
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:09,708
Sorry. I was just
messing with you.

179
00:09:09,791 --> 00:09:11,750
Sei...

180
00:09:13,083 --> 00:09:15,458
That's right. The noise
isn't coming from the motor.

181
00:09:15,541 --> 00:09:17,375
It must be something else.

182
00:09:17,458 --> 00:09:19,791
No, I don't think
that'll be necessary...

183
00:09:19,875 --> 00:09:21,208
It's probably just the machines

184
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:23,458
not being used to
these conditions.

185
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:26,791
No prob. I'll go ahead and
put it on the top of the list.

186
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,916
Must be hearing things.

187
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:54,833
I've been looking
all over for you...

188
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:55,833
Hm?

189
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:58,916
Feels nice and cold, doesn't it?

190
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,916
Yeah, a little.

191
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:05,833
You're so weird sometimes.

192
00:10:05,916 --> 00:10:10,166
You know you haven't changed one
bit since the first time we met.

193
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,750
Ever since I came
to this country,

194
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:14,291
so many different things
have surprised me...

195
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:17,000
Never thought I'd
make it this far.

196
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:21,625
In fact, being here like this
almost seems like a lie.

197
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:26,750
I wish everyday
were like this one.

198
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:29,125
Oh yeah?

199
00:10:29,208 --> 00:10:30,958
Say, Jo...

200
00:10:33,541 --> 00:10:35,041
I...

201
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:39,750
Sometimes I wonder what you
were like before we met...

202
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:41,833
If I had to guess,

203
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:46,125
I would think you were
probably fighting every day...

204
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:50,333
But, whether you're working
or not, you always seem to be

205
00:10:50,416 --> 00:10:53,125
fighting in some
way or another...

206
00:10:54,416 --> 00:10:59,125
It's like you're just not
interested in anything else...

207
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:02,333
But I suppose that's
not a bad thing!

208
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:46,666
I fight for you, Meg.

209
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:49,500
Really?

210
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:53,833
Yeah. You saved
my life after all.

211
00:11:53,916 --> 00:11:56,833
