212
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:00,541
Yeah, I do.

213
00:12:01,791 --> 00:12:03,000
Jo...

214
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,166
I'm happy...

215
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:11,291
I'm very happy to have met you.

216
00:12:25,625 --> 00:12:27,125
Hah! I'm in!

217
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:29,625
Wow, this place is huge!

218
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:42,458
Jo. What are you
doing down there?

219
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:43,708
I can hear it.

220
00:12:43,791 --> 00:12:47,583
I don't understand.
You can hear what?

221
00:12:49,791 --> 00:12:51,625
What is this?

222
00:12:53,541 --> 00:12:55,041
Your attention please.

223
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:56,375
We will now be resetting

224
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:59,375
all of the facilities here
at Tokyo Fortune Island.

225
00:12:59,458 --> 00:13:01,375
We are terribly sorry
for the inconvenience...

226
00:13:01,458 --> 00:13:03,083
Meg. Let's go.

227
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:04,833
What?

228
00:13:04,916 --> 00:13:06,875
Please gather your
belongings and make your way

229
00:13:06,958 --> 00:13:09,416
to the park's exit in
an orderly fashion.

230
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,250
Shuttle buses will be
waiting there to drive you

231
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:13,625
back to the mainland
and to your vehicles.

232
00:13:13,708 --> 00:13:16,083
For security reasons,
we ask that you help us

233
00:13:16,166 --> 00:13:19,166
avoid any possible dangers
by refraining from smoking.

234
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:21,208
No smoking?

235
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:22,875
This must be the reason.

236
00:13:22,958 --> 00:13:25,708
That looks nasty, ugh.

237
00:13:25,791 --> 00:13:27,250
No one's talking,

238
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:28,833
but it looks like there was
an oil tanker accident nearby.

239
00:13:28,916 --> 00:13:32,000
Oh, okay. So that's
why we can't smoke.

240
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:33,958
Try lightin' up a butt here,
and one stray spark

241
00:13:34,041 --> 00:13:36,125
could turn the place
into a blazing inferno.

242
00:13:36,208 --> 00:13:38,125
Seriously?!

243
00:13:38,208 --> 00:13:41,000
"Any possible dangers?"
If they know there's trouble,

244
00:13:41,083 --> 00:13:42,500
they should just say so!

245
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:45,208
The truth would only cause
unnecessary panic, Meg...

246
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:47,625
C'mon... We should
get moving too.

247
00:13:57,291 --> 00:14:00,666
The oil fence is 60% complete.
However, the flow rate

248
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:02,958
is accelerating faster
than anticipated.

249
00:14:03,041 --> 00:14:06,000
The shuttle buses have arrived.
Commence evacuation.

250
00:14:07,166 --> 00:14:08,208
What the?!

251
00:14:09,541 --> 00:14:11,916
Everyone please line
up single file here.

252
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:15,250
Remember to keep hold of
your children at all times.

253
00:14:33,583 --> 00:14:34,875
You guys need to
learn to chill out

254
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:37,375
and enjoy yourselves sometimes.

255
00:14:37,458 --> 00:14:40,625
You got a point but how can we,
when all the chicks are gone?

256
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:42,791
Look dude, I had to work
for my dad for a whole month

257
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:44,875
so he'd use his
connections to get us in.

258
00:14:44,958 --> 00:14:47,583
You could show a
little gratitude...

259
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:51,416
Whoa, dudes, check that out!

260
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,333
Please tell me it's a couple
of hot, young mermaids

261
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:54,000
looking to party.

262
00:14:54,083 --> 00:14:55,500
Whoa! Mermaids?

263
00:14:57,708 --> 00:14:58,708
What?

264
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:12,708
Crap!

265
00:15:14,375 --> 00:15:15,875
No way!

266
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:23,458
This can't be good.

267
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:25,916
Yeah, and the trailer's on
the other side of the bay.

268
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,500
With these flames
as high as they are,

269
00:15:27,583 --> 00:15:29,291
there's no way we can get to it.

270
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:30,666
What's gonna happen?

271
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:32,791
I dunno. Probably nothing.

272
00:15:32,875 --> 00:15:34,166
I don't get you people!

273
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:37,208
How can you be so calm
at a time like this?

274
00:15:37,291 --> 00:15:38,291
Let's get to the roof for now

275
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:40,416
and hope a rescue team
comes to get us.

276
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,541
Good idea. Let's hurry.

277
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:48,625
We're in luck!
Everyone get to the chopper!

278
00:15:48,708 --> 00:15:50,541
What, so you're
a pilot now, too?

279
00:15:50,625 --> 00:15:52,041
Heh. Yeah!

280
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:56,166
What the hell?!

281
00:16:00,625 --> 00:16:03,166
Ah, shit...! Not the chopper!

282
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,000
What...

283
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:05,250
...is that?

284
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:07,833
I think it's an octopus.
You saw its tentacles.

285
00:16:07,916 --> 00:16:10,125
Or a gigantic squid.

286
00:16:10,208 --> 00:16:12,625
It's a damn tentacle beast.

287
00:16:14,208 --> 00:16:16,750
What do you mean a few
people were left behind?

288
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:20,000
That's what the shuttle
bus driver reported.

289
00:16:20,083 --> 00:16:22,208
I'm afraid it's hopeless
to attempt a rescue

290
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:23,625
in that flaming ocean.

291
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:25,791
Understood... but
the real problem is in

292
00:16:25,875 --> 00:16:29,708
whom to blame for this...
gross negligence.

293
00:16:29,791 --> 00:16:33,125
I seem to recall an
environmental preservation group

294
00:16:33,208 --> 00:16:35,375
who opposed this project.

295
00:16:35,458 --> 00:16:37,916
Pin it on them... Got it?

296
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,291
Yes, sir.

297
00:16:39,375 --> 00:16:41,125
Gather all of the
evidence we'll need

298
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:43,416
and release it at tonight's
press conference.

299
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,166
I'm counting on you.

300
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:49,333
Let me go!

301
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:54,708
Sei!

302
00:16:58,375 --> 00:17:00,958
Sorry for being so heavy.

303
00:17:01,041 --> 00:17:03,916
We got ourselves one
slimy situation...

304
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,500
This is no time for
stupid jokes, Leo!

305
00:17:06,583 --> 00:17:08,625
How are we gonna
get off this island?

306
00:17:08,708 --> 00:17:10,000
You probably made it angry

307
00:17:10,083 --> 00:17:11,750
when you ate its parents
for dinner the other night!

308
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:14,916
Shut up, Amy! That
doesn't even make any sense!

309
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:21,833
Hey boys.

310
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,458
Why didn't you get on the bus?

311
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:26,958
We--We were just
sneaking around...

312
00:17:27,041 --> 00:17:27,875
And...

313
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:29,375
I was smoking a cigarette...

314
00:17:29,458 --> 00:17:32,500
Then the whole place
just went up in flames!

315
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:35,750
Ah ha. So you're the ones
that started the fire.

316
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:37,125
Yeah? Well, this
wouldn't have happened

317
00:17:37,208 --> 00:17:38,541
if we had just left
with everyone else!

318
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:41,375
Shut up, assface! Don't try
to blame all this on me!

319
00:17:41,458 --> 00:17:43,041
I didn't force you
to stay behind.

320
00:17:43,125 --> 00:17:44,666
But you were--

321
00:17:45,791 --> 00:17:47,333
Shut your traps.

322
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:51,333
I'm sorry!
Please don't shoot me!

323
00:17:52,958 --> 00:17:54,333
Gimme that.

324
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,666
What are you
planning on doing, Jo?

325
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:01,958
Amy. Be ready to go as
soon as I get in the air.

326
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:03,916
Ready for what?

327
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:07,041
We're gonna kill that
damn tentacle beast.

328
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,916
She's so cool!

329
00:18:19,375 --> 00:18:20,375
Jo!

330
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:22,833
Jo!

331
00:18:25,375 --> 00:18:26,375
Oh, no, no!

332
00:18:26,458 --> 00:18:29,250
She let herself
get thrown on purpose.

333
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:30,791
What for?

334
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:32,125
What for...?

335
00:18:32,208 --> 00:18:34,166
Because she needed a way
to get past the flames...

336
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:36,708
Damn, she can be
reckless sometimes.

337
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:38,333
Amy. Get on your laptop

338
00:18:38,416 --> 00:18:40,541
and open the trailer's
hanger for Jo.

339
00:18:40,625 --> 00:18:43,750
Oh okay. Now I see what
Jo was talking about!

340
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:47,666
Someone might want
to fill in Meg.

341
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:49,208
I don't think she gets it.

342
00:18:51,666 --> 00:18:53,333
I think the oil has
seeped into the building.

343
00:18:53,416 --> 00:18:55,541
This whole place
is going up soon.

344
00:18:55,625 --> 00:18:58,625
No, please make it stop!
I don't want to die a virgin!

345
00:18:58,708 --> 00:19:00,458
Someone save us!

346
00:19:00,541 --> 00:19:01,666
Knock it off you twerps!

347
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:04,083
You're whining like
a bunch of little girls!

348
00:19:04,166 --> 00:19:06,000
Ah, there she is!

349
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:12,000
I don't believe it! Jo's alive!

350
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:19,625
--You made it!
--She's alive!

351
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:21,291
You guys okay?

352
00:19:45,875 --> 00:19:48,166
The bastard's regenerating.

353
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:51,958
What the...?

354
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:53,958
I can't see a thing!

355
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:36,541
Gross!

356
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:44,291
Uh...! He's covered in oil!

357
00:20:44,375 --> 00:20:47,583
I can't believe this, I just
waxed him the other day.

358
00:20:47,666 --> 00:20:49,666
Sorry Leo, couldn't avoid it.

359
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,541
You can at least
help me re-wax him.

360
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:52,916
Come on you two.

361
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,625
What matters is that
we're safe now.

362
00:20:54,708 --> 00:20:56,750
But my poor Jango!

363
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:59,500
Looks like you need
a waxing too, Leo.

364
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,916
Thankfully, those
that we couldn't save

365
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,791
before the fire erupted
managed to escape unharmed.

366
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,291
While we are
currently investigating

367
00:21:11,375 --> 00:21:13,708
the exact cause of this
horrible accident,

368
00:21:13,791 --> 00:21:16,166
we have received
word that the ONPOT,

369
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:18,875
the Organization for the
Nature Preservation of Tokyo,

370
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,791
were directly involved.

371
00:21:20,875 --> 00:21:22,666
If these accusations
are found to be true,

372
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:26,291
then the ONPOT is guilty of
multiple terrorist acts,

373
00:21:26,375 --> 00:21:28,833
and I assure you all,
we will prosecute them

374
00:21:28,916 --> 00:21:31,583
to the fullest
extent of the law.

375
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:34,541
You should just be thankful

376
00:21:34,625 --> 00:21:36,666
you weren't seriously
injured, or worse!

377
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,208
No kidding!

378
00:21:39,375 --> 00:21:40,625
That's what happens

379
00:21:40,708 --> 00:21:42,875
when you decide to go
somewhere fun without us.

380
00:21:48,416 --> 00:21:51,375
Squid! Not squid!

381
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:52,458
What's wrong, Kyo?

382
00:21:52,541 --> 00:21:54,083
Oh man. Get a grip!

383
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:56,916
I hate squid.

384
00:22:14,208 --> 00:22:18,000
I don't know why I can't move

385
00:22:18,083 --> 00:22:21,875
My mind is lost in this cloud

386
00:22:21,958 --> 00:22:29,250
No one even hears my voice
and my tears fall to the ground

387
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:36,875
It's like my feelings of
loneliness are falling too

388
00:22:36,958 --> 00:22:42,166
The truth is that we
all just want to smile

389
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:46,333
and smile with each other

390
00:22:46,416 --> 00:22:49,625
It hurts inside
when we don't...

391
00:22:49,708 --> 00:22:53,250
we don't... we don't
know what to say

392
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:58,000
I only hope that
someone will be there,

393
00:22:58,083 --> 00:23:02,083
and be watching over me

394
00:23:02,166 --> 00:23:04,083
so take my hand,

395
00:23:04,166 --> 00:23:12,875
we'll walk tonight
underneath the sky

396
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:33,666
An unknown enemy hiding
in the darkness.

397
00:23:33,750 --> 00:23:37,208
A battle that's not quite
nightmare or illusion.

398
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:40,208
And Jo is drawn
into another world.

399
00:23:40,291 --> 00:23:44,208
Next Burst Angel:
The Man With No Name.

